Certified Primary School Teachers Needed for Abu Dhabi International Schools
Teach at a beautiful International Private School in the city of Al-Ain, UAE. Al Ain, also known as the Garden City due to its greenery, is the second largest city in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi and the fourth largest city in the United Arab Emirates.We are looking for certified and experienced teachers to teach kindergarten through Grade 5 classes. You'll be teaching at a newly established school that follows a US teaching curriculum. You'll not only have the opportunity to make a difference abroad, but you'll also be compensated with a lucrative salary package that provides you with an excellent rate of pay and some amazing job perks.Start Date: September 1, 2014Note that we are beginning interviews now in order for teachers to get their paperwork processed for their UAE visa.Basic Position RequirementsPlease have a look at the basic requirements for our positions to see if you qualify for our positions.Native English speakers from Canada and the United States onlyUniversity Degree in Education/Primary Education/Early Childhood Education.3 years of full time teaching experience with young learnersCertified to teach Grades 1 to 5 in United States or CanadaYou must be between 25 and 45 years of age. Please note that if you do not meet the above-mentioned requirements, we cannot consider you for this position. Salary and Benefits PackageYour teaching package includes:Furnished accommodation with paid water and electricity billsAnnual round trip ticketsWork transportation is free of chargeMedical and health insurance providedA non-taxable monthly salary of 8,000AED to 9,000AED, based on experience and qualifications.If you're interested in this incredible opportunity, please don't delay in submitting your application. We have a limited number of positions on offer, and we expect that they will go quickly!
